title: Spain counts 1,500 new coronavirus cases in one day
text: Madrid, Mar 14 (AFP) Spain confirmed more than 1,500 new cases of coronavirus between Friday and Saturday raising its total to 5,753 cases, the second-highest number in Europe after Italy. The country was expected to declare a state of emergency on Saturday to try to mobilise resources to combat the virus, which has so far killed 136 people in Spain. (AFP) CPS
